author: Amai Ta. Yume
text:
This SC was so long I couldn't even leave. Yes I do have some business here and there, but I couldn't stop listening to her. I tried watching other streams to see, but Rushia is definitely the one I always stay and come back too. She really appreciates every message and that always show in her efforts. I'm actually glad that I met her through other translations clips. It's sad I do not know Nihonggo yet, but I'm still learning. One day, I'll really send a superchat through my own effort. I hope when that time comes,  she's still there. Even if she's not, I'll always wait. It's like a light filled up my tunnel. Sometimes I forgot what to do in my life but Rushia is one of those parts that keeps on thinking that Japan is a great place to be.

So with that in mind, I want to thank everyone's support for her. Even if I'm fairly new and not a member, You're actions made Rushia who she is today. And Rushia, I want to thank you for your heart whelming response for those you read. For having fun in Minecraft despite thinking that you're gonna make a house full of TNT, but instead likes too see destruction in the mountains XD. Take care Rushia, See you tomorrow! Even if something happens I'll be their as a subscriber and a viewer count. One day I'll become a member. Daisuki! Nano desu! 

PS: I don't know if she reached Top Superchat yet, But even if it's a glimpse, I might as well give a super chat when Rushia does achieve it and say that everything she's done is worth everything for me and her fans. :)
